main event: The witness observed an orange crescent-shaped light that appeared to be a self-luminous object near Andrews, South Carolina on January 21, 1969.
interesting points: The object was initially motionless, then started moving at a high rate of speed north, then west to east.
The object seemed to rise in the sky as it moved east and disappeared from sight within a few seconds.
The witness reported that the movement and characteristics of the object were quite different from a star or plane.
The object was estimated to be about 10 inches in diameter.
The witness reported no sound coming from the object.
